Jimbo's is a Mexican/American 'eatery'. I say eatery because it is not just a hamburger place, but serves a variety of food from both cultures. They have several locations in Manhattan. Perhaps elsewhere too but I don't know because I've only been there a few times. However the food is good, it's fast and the service is great. I like also because I get to practice my Spanish, and the waitress is kind enough to speak Spanish back to me, even though she is fluent in English. Her name is Iris. The one I go to is just off 145th street in Harlem. You can't go wrong at Jimbo's. 😎

Great prices and good food...  Like most budget food establishments, you tend to get 2/3 of the most important qualities of food service (good food/good service/good prices). Jimbos has great good and good prices, the process of receiving the food however needs improvement.  Apparently they are still in 1991 and only take cash and it will take forever to get your food. However, it's worth the wait. Everything is made to order and by Cooks that have mastered their craft.  Simply put, enjoy Jimbo's when you're not in a rush.
